    11/21/2020

    It's been a long week, working long hours, and I needed to get the family fed on Thursday night so I did an Uber Eats order. I found the price to be on the higher side, but they offered delivery and Sozo does not.. I would order from here again, but only the things I liked. I probably won't try anything new next time.

    There were some great items and some terrible items. The spicy scallop hand roll was terrible, smelled fishy and didn't taste good. Sadly, It was tossed out (not something I ever do, I don't waste food but I just didn't like it and no one else was willing to touch it after I complained).

    The stars of the night were, The Crunch Mango roll, and both the yellowtail and yellowtail jalapeo. I really enjoyed both of these.

    Orange blossom was okay, omega 3 ok, I'd order both again. Garlic edamame also okay, but not for me. Felt like it was cooked with Costco jarred garlic, which I'm not a fan of. I'll skip that next time, but the kids ate it without complaint.

    I won't order the salmon belly again (fishy smelling), as was the sushi omakasa. Salmon nigiri is the kids favorite and it looked dried out, thin, and was not tasty. They don't usually complain about quality and they did with the nigiri. So I was disappointed in that.

    Overall the price was high for my order and given the things we didn't like, I felt it was wasted money. While I'm okay with high prices if the quality is there, I felt a few fails in the options we chose, but I am happy to order from here again. I found a few items I really enjoyed and will happily order them for delivery in the future.

    This place is worth a try. Next time I may call to ask for recommendations from the restaurant. I usually do that when I dine in, why not do it now.

    The sushi loot! ALL Yellowtail was delicious!!

    Delivery order, with the winners circled.

    Follows COVID precautions -- masks, online ordering, social distancing...I love it! Sadly it's only open for takeout and 1 table of outdoor dining! They only take Cash, Venmo or PayPal at the moment. I saw that they take credit card, but there's some type of charge. I just opted to pay with cash. But they were super friendly and great customer service.

    We got three different rolls and an appetizer, but I can't remember the last roll's name so....

    1. Chicken Karaage : good sized portions. I was expecting the classic nugget style karaage, but this was more of a tender. But still juicy and crunchy exterior. 4/5

    2. Golden California Roll : this was good too. Crunchy tempura, not soggy or soft and the inner ingredients were fresh. 3/5

    3. Ocean Roll (?) : I think that this was best roll. The fish in the roll was fresh and it came out like if we had ordered it from the sushi bar. 4/5

    They also gave us miso soup since we ate there. Disclaimer: we only ordered one!

    Hopefully this place makes it through the pandemic, so I can see what the rest of the menu is like! It's got some different creative rolls that we'd like to try.

    Outdoor Seating! Only 1 table for now

So I called the server to inquire and he said he'd check. Then he brought out a plate with one shrimp tempura. Weird. The veggie tempura was good though. The batter was light and the veggies were fresh.

    Overall it was okay. The service was okay. The portions were fine.

  • Kari C.

    Elite '2021

    Walnut Creek, CA
    369
    749
    1493
    7/31/2019
    4 photos

    This used to be Sendo Sushi, one of our local faves, but it is now under new management. The sushi chefs and waitstaff are all new. The interior is largely unchanged, the biggest differences is no more dingy dark carpet and all the photos near the door, including Jerry Rice.

    We started off with a salmon collar, which was one of the best items this evening. There was a generous amount of char and the salmon was pretty silky.

    DH was so stoked they had salmon & yellowtail belly nigiri. Both cuts looked beautiful and they were generous portions. The "fusion" salmon ($7 for two pieces) had a seasoned oil on top of it, which added flavor, but it was hard to tell what the base flavor was! The yellowtail belly ($7 also) was kinda chewy and had a fishy aftertaste. DH was not pleased. "Not supposed to be like that. Worst yellowtail belly I've ever had!"

    The rice is something else too. Not balanced and too sour. Even the little one refused to eat it.

    The Omega 3 roll ($13.95) was absolutely beautiful. Sendo never had rolls as gorgeous as this one, with microgreens no less! This roll was topped with salmon and a bit of crushed pineapple. I think the inside was avocado and salmon? The fish seemed fresh, but there wasn't a whole lot of flavor. The roll didn't taste balanced either. Too much tang?

    The Dragon roll ($12.95) was also nice looking. DH liked the taste of this one. The eel wasn't the most tender and the tempura shrimp wasn't as crisp as I'd like, but that's nitpicking. It's perfectly acceptable given the price.

    We didn't have any leftovers and sorely missed our faves from Sendo. It isn't that great of a value now. It's more in line with the other TriValley sushi restaurants. Servers were brand new, so we cut them some slack for slow service. It wasn't very crowded for dinner. Parking was easy in their lot. DH says he wants to try then again once they're more established and order different things like their cooked food. Maybe we'll find new favs.

  • Augusto T.

    Elite '2021

    Dublin, CA
    632
    892

    1/1/2020

    Lunch was enjoyable.

    I stopped by for a quick and casual chirashi bowl for lunch. The included soup and salad were both above average. The dressing for the salad was delicious and the miso soup had a great base and was served satisfyingly hot.

    The fish in the chirashi bowl had good layers of flavor and tasted fresh. Even the sometimes bland ebi was appropriately shrimpy. I appreciated the inclusion of tsukemono in the bowl. The rice was seasoned OK, but if I'm being nitpicky it wasn't perfect (each grain was somehow slighly undercooked and hard in the center and slighly soft on the outside, I've managed this surprising result a few times myself..., but here it was not too bad and still enjoyable. Again I'm nitpicking). I was full and happy after finishing my lunch.

    Service was friendly and attentive with the restaurant largely empty.

    I'm definitely interested in coming back and trying more, but not sure what I will choose next. Sometimes I wish these types of restaurants would specialize a bit more.
